pr_body:
Adds two rules for `cargo`:

- `cargo`: for those who are too used to simply type `make` and are fucked every time they want `cargo` to actually compile their project;
- `cargo_no_command`: fixes spelling mistakes, similar to the `git_not_command` rule.

Route 53 has defined their `MaxItems` pagination field as a string which leads to issues when passing the `page-size` flag to the cli as it will convert the value to an integer. This PR adds a hook to automatically convert the `MaxItems` field back into a string in the case that the operation expects it to be a string.

Fixes: https://github.com/boto/botocore/issues/1063

@JordonPhillips @stealthycoin @kyleknap @jamesls

This adds `EPDPlatform._from_platform_tag`.

This is only of limited use, since platform_tag does not have enough information, but this may be used to get an EPDPlatform instance from a non-Enthought python. Mostly useful for tests in tateru.

@sjagoe

@pde had some stylistic concerns around #5639 which this PR addresses. I updated the docstring and split some of the code into a separate function. Rather making the code look something like:
```
if certname:
    new_name = certname
else:
    new_name = _strip_wildcard(domains[0])
...
def _strip_wildcard(domain):
    return domain[2:] if util.is_wildcard_domain(domains) else domain
```
I further split up the function moving the logical piece of determining the name for the lineage into its own function. This splits up `obtain_and_enroll_certificate` even more and better documents at a high level what is being done.
